Author: @Mikecorsale
Comment: The metaphor of this game is that the entire facility is a human being. The boy is a carcinogen, a seemingly innocuous entity that is infiltrating the heavily guarded body, deactivated infrastructure as he goes, until finally he frees the cancerous tumour to wreak havoc on the whole body. The doctors, looking on and realising they can no longer contain this tumour, instead coax it to its ejection point and out to die at the lake, as without a host, cancer dies. The alternative ending is the creature/parasite/boy pulls the plug on this persons life early on, there’s no protracted cancer battle. Genius stuff 👏🏽

Author: @haltux
Comment:
I find your interpretation of the secret ending rather convoluted and, to say the least, very speculative. A way more obvious interpretation is that the boy unplug himself from the control we, as a player, have on him. Which is a pretty satisfying 'secret' ending. But that does not explain all the rest, in particular the huddle. 

It's sad that such a great game has such an obscure and ultimately vain scenario. I admit I can be too stupid to find out what is going on, but when even when you read everything on the internet you don't find any satisfying explanation, then there is clearly something wrong with the way the game was written. It's a bit like the Witness, after several years noone has really understood this game.

Author: @spongeintheshoe
Comment: I’d like to propose another character, who I call the Continuity Lemming. While the Rational Decision-Maker plans for the future, and the Instant Gratification Monkey focuses on the present, the Continuity Lemming looks toward the past. Specifically, it wants to keep doing whatever you’re already doing. After all, if you’re still computing logic, then whatever you’ve been doing hasn’t killed you yet. As such, the Lemming will resist any sort of change in behavior just as hard as the Monkey resists doing something that isn’t fun. But if you can fight the Lemming and stay dedicated to a new behavior for long enough, then eventually, that new behavior stops being a new behavior, and just becomes what you were already doing, at which point the Lemming will be just as dedicated to maintaining this new behavior as it was to fighting it. When the Monkey and the Lemming are working together, they can form a seemingly-insurmountable tag team, but if you can get the Lemming on your side, it can be a powerful ally against the Monkey… although it can’t fight the Monkey _for_ you, and if you drop the ball, the Monkey can take advantage of that opening to turn the Lemming against you.

Author: @adelinamikayelyan7488
Comment: This talk offers a fascinating look at the internal battle between the “Instant Gratification Monkey” and the “Rational Decision-Maker.” The “Dark Playground” concept really resonated with me, especially when he describes the way we end up distracted, even though we know there’s important work to be done. It made me realize how much of procrastination isn’t about being lazy but about avoiding discomfort. What stood out even more is how he shows that procrastination is a universal human flaw, not a personal failure. It’s reassuring to know that even the most successful people face this struggle in some form. I think what makes his talk even more impactful is the way he encourages us to view procrastination not as something that prevents us from accomplishing tasks, but as something we can learn to manage. Understanding this gives a sense of control and a clearer path forward, even when we’re caught in that mental tug-of-war.

Author: @tinyfatgiant
Comment:
Insights:
1. Universal Procrastination: Urban contends that everyone procrastinates in some form, even if they appear organised. When deadlines are absent, the impact is hidden but potentially more harmful.
2. Emotional Toll: Procrastination carries guilt, regret, and a sense of wasted potential, harming personal fulfilment over time.
3. Role of Unstructured Goals: Many deeply important life pursuits (entrepreneurship, health, relationships) lack explicit deadlines, so these can remain perpetually on hold.
4. Self-Awareness: Urban’s comedic style might mask a more serious point: procrastination can make people passive observers of their own aspirations if they do not consciously intervene.
5. “Non-Procrastinators” Do Not Exist: Everyone, in some area of life, must wrestle with the impulse to delay or avoid tasks.

Subject: Proposal for Investigating Angular Momentum-Induced Lift in Rotational Systems

Dear [Recipient's Name],

I hope this message finds you well. I am writing to share a concept I have been developing over the past seven years, inspired by the principles of angular momentum and precession, and to seek your insights or potential collaboration on this project.

The design consists of a metal, four-axle crossbar structure, with each axle supporting solid metal disks capable of spinning at high speeds. Each wheel face's normal vector is parallel to its respective axle, ensuring that angular momentum is directed outward from the system's center. The system employs an 8-wheel configuration distributed across upper and lower decks:

Upper and Lower Deck Design: The upper deck’s wheels have outward-pointing angular momentum, while the lower deck’s wheels have momentum directed inward. Both decks are balanced to maintain equal inertias, contributing to system stability.

Deck Rotation and Power: The upper and lower decks rotate with respect to each other, and both the deck rotation and wheel spin are powered by DC motors for precise control.

Potential Addition of a 9th Wheel: To enhance stability, I am considering a centrally located 9th wheel facing upward, unlike the others. This may help counteract any undesired deviations in the system’s behavior.

Two-Part Mechanism:

Gravity-Induced Precession: When torque is applied, the system experiences both an upward force and angular velocity about the z-axis, resulting in precession.

Potential Angular to Linear Momentum Conversion: By applying torque in the same direction as the angular momentum and rotating about the system's central vertical axis (z-axis), vertical lift has been observed. This lift may result from the exchange of angular momentum for linear momentum, a dynamic that invites further exploration within classical Newtonian physics.

Initial tests using a single spinning wheel powered by a hand grinder have shown that applying torque aligned with angular momentum, along with system rotation about the z-axis, leads to observable lift. This suggests that refining the 8-wheel design and exploring the impact of a 9th wheel could offer insights into achieving continuous lift.

I am currently working on optimizing the balance between axle length, wheel momentum, and precession rate. Additionally, implementing analog PID loops and differential amplifiers will help stabilize and fine-tune the system for more consistent results.

I would greatly appreciate your thoughts on this idea or any guidance you could offer regarding further experimental approaches or theoretical considerations.

கொஞ்சங் கூட மனிதாபிமானற்ற ஜென்மங்கள்.குத்துயிரும் குலை உயிருமாக பெண்கள் குழந்தைகள்.அவர்கள் என்ன கேட்கிறார்கள்?..எங்களை நிம்மதியா வாழ விடுங்கடா!..அவர்களுக்கான வாழ்விடத்தைத் தான் அவர்கள் கேட்கிறார்கள்.ஹமாஸை அந்த மக்களிடமிருந்து பிரித்தால் மொத்தமாக காஸாவை கைப்பற்றலாம் என நினைக்கிறது அமெரிக்கா!..அதற்காகத் தான் ஹமாஸை குறி வைக்கிறான் ட்ரம்ப்.செத்தாலும் எங்களது உயிர் இந்த மண்ணில் தான் என்கிறார்கள் காஸா மக்கள்.இந்த நேரத்தில் தான் போர் நிறுத்த ஒப்பந்தம் ரத்து என்கிறது அமெரிக்கா!..எந்த நேரத்திலும் காஸாவில் எதுவும் நடக்கலாம்.நீண்ட நாட்களுக்குப் பிறகு தங்களது சொந்த வீடு வந்த மக்களை நிம்மதியாக தூங்கக் கூட விடாமல் மன நோயாளியாக மாற்றுகிறது அமெரிக்கா!..யோசித்துப் பார்த்தால் ஒவ்வொரு காஸா பிரஜையும் இப்போது எந்த மன நிலையில் இருப்பார்கள்?..இது ஆண்டவனின் சோதனையா அல்லது இரண்டு அயோக்கியர்கள் தரும் வேதனையா?..எப்போதும் போல இப்போதும் இந்த உலகம் வேடிக்கை மட்டும்  தான் பார்க்குமா?..மனிதனை மனிதனே வேட்டையாடத் துடிக்கிறான்.பெண்கள் குழந்தைகள் என பார்க்காமல் அத்தனை பேரையும் ஒழித்துக்கட்டத் துடிக்கிறான்.இது தான் மனித நீதியா?..வேடிக்கை பார்க்கும் நமக்குக் கூட மனசாட்சி உறுத்தவில்லையா?..மனிதாபிமானமே  இல்லையா?..மனிதனாகப் பிறந்த ஒவ்வொருவருக்கும் தார்மீகக் கடமையில்லையா?..இந்தக் கயவர்களை தட்டிக் கேட்க யாருமே இல்லையா?..துவண்டு போன அந்த அப்பாவி மக்கள் நம்மைப் பார்த்துத் தான் கேட்கிறார்கள்.

அரேபிய தலைவர்கள் அல்லாஹ்வின் இந்த வார்த்தையை பின்பற்றிலே போதும். இன்னும், நீங்கள் எல்லோரும் அல்லாஹ்வின் கயிற்றை வலுவாக பற்றிப் பிடித்துக் கொள்ளுங்கள்; நீங்கள் பிரிந்தும் விடாதீர்கள்; அல்லாஹ் உங்களுக்குக் கொடுத்த நிஃமத்களை (அருள் கொடைகளை) நினைத்துப் பாருங்கள்; நீங்கள் பகைவர்களாய் இருந்தீர்கள் - உங்கள் இதயங்களை அன்பினால் பிணைத்து; அவனது அருளால் நீங்கள் சகோதரர்களாய் ஆகிவிட்டீர்கள்; இன்னும், நீங்கள் (நரக) நெருப்புக் குழியின் கரை மீதிருந்தீர்கள்; அதனின்றும் அவன் உங்களைக் காப்பாற்றினான் - நீங்கள் நேர் வழி பெறும் பொருட்டு அல்லாஹ் இவ்வாறு தன் ஆயத்களை - வசனங்களை உங்களுக்கு தெளிவாக்குகிறான்.

- (திருக்குர்ஆன் 3:103
